            <tr>
              <td colspan="5">
                <p class="ia-table-text"><b>What is the problem under consideration? Why is government intervention necessary?</b></p>
                <p class="ia-table-text">Lower caseloads for official receivers (officials dealing with the administration of bankruptcies and companies in compulsory liquidation) than forecast is leading to a forecast operational deficit of around £1.2m in 2016/17. The problem under consideration is the need to raise fees to cover costs. In addition, the fees need to be set in such a way as to comply with "Managing Public Money" principles.  Government intervention is the only means available for raising income for the Insolvency Service, if this it not possible the deficit would continue to be funded by the Department of Business, Innovation and Skills and ultimately by taxpayers. </p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table>
        </content>
