      <paragraph>
        <num>32.</num>
        <content>
          <p>The proposed increases would only apply to new insolvency cases from commencement of the new Fees Order (expected to be 16 November 2015), there would be no retrospective charging or other similar provision.</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph>
        <num>33.</num>
        <content>
          <p>The new SOS fees would only be charged where the insolvency petition was made on or after 16 November 2015. Cases commenced prior to this but still in progress would still be charged under the previous bands.</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph>
        <num>34.</num>
        <content>
          <p>All other things equal the lower bands will reduce the average amount of SOS fee received per case and by assumption reduce the degree of cross subsidisation of cases.</p>
        </content>
